race.comment: STILL AVAILABLE (7) is better than last start when seventh (30.30) from Box 6 at this track over 520m. Goes very well from this draw with six wins and three minor placings from 13 starts. Worth another chance. LEONI BALE (1) finished fifth last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 457m at Temora, taking a Grade 4/5 in a head turning 25.73. Smart winner two back and looks a key chance on that form. WEST ROCK CASEY (8) has been in super consistent form recently with two minors on end before breaking through for an overdue win (29.75) at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning seven races. Will go close here with a clear run. UNLEASH BEETSON (6) continues to race well and is sure to be competitive again.
